**Original Issue**: #1534 class then 'use strict'
**Opened by**: @satyr
**Milestone**: [as soon as a patch is available](https://github.com/jashkenas/coffee-script/issues?milestone=10&state=open)
on July 20, 2011

The `'use strict'` directive was being displaced inside `Class` bodies:

``` coffeescript
class then 'use strict'
```

``` javascript
(function() {
  function _Class() {}
  'use strict';
  return _Class;
})();

```

 As `use strict` is only in effect when it is the first line in a function statement/declaration or Global code, this would prevent `strict` from applying.

