`static` is now properly bound to `C`.

Example:

```
o.scope.parameter v = v.compile o for *v in vars unless splats
```

instead of

```
o.scope.parameter vars[i] = v.compile o for v, i in vars unless splats
```

The example compiles to this code:

```
var _i, _len;
if (!splats) {
  for (_i = 0, _len = vars.length; _i < _len; _i++) {
    o.scope.parameter(vars[_i] = vars[_i].compile(o));
  }
}
```

The star means that every access and assignment to `v` should be compiled to an array access.

