Following up on #1309, I thought I'd add some unit tests for `eval`. I noticed that the simple test

```
ok CoffeeScript.eval 'true'
```

was failing because without the `bare` option, `eval` was generating the JS

```
(function() {
  var _;
  _ = true;
}).call(this);
```

Since it doesn't make sense for `_` to be used that way when it's within the function scope, this patch removes `_` and adds a `return` when the `bare` option isn't set. Also adds a test case. (More `eval` tests to follow, since we don't have any good way of testing the REPL directly yet...)

As I mentioned in issue #928, using an implicit object in a function call puts the parser in a weird state:

